title: Campus Spring Festival
description: Annual spring celebration with music, food, and activities for all students and faculty members.

title: Research Symposium
description: Showcase of student and faculty research projects from all departments. Opportunity to network and collaborate.

title: Basketball Tournament
description: Interdepartmental basketball competition. Teams of 5 players, round-robin format followed by knockout stages.

title: Cultural Dance Showcase
description: Performances highlighting traditional dances from around the world. Showcase of cultural diversity on campus.

title: Web Development Bootcamp
description: Intensive three-day workshop covering HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and modern frameworks like React.

title: Alumni Networking Night
description: Networking event connecting current students with successful alumni from various industries.

title: Environmental Science Lecture
description: Guest lecture on climate change and sustainable development by renowned environmental scientist Dr. Green.

title: Creative Writing Workshop
description: Hands-on workshop for aspiring writers to develop their craft through exercises and feedback.

title: Yoga and Meditation Session
description: Relaxation session to help students manage stress during final exam period.
